parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Takata airbag recall issues can cause the airbags to deploy unexpectedly or not deploy at all in the event of a crash, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Unexpected airbag deployment
failure of airbags to deploy in a crash
injuries or fatalities due to airbag malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
injuries or fatalities due to airbag malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracking of the dashboard can lead to expensive repairs and potentially affect the functionality of the vehicle's systems.
symptoms: Cracking of the dashboard
especially behind the instrument cluster.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission control module can cause the transmission to shift into limp mode, leading to sudden loss of power and speed, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission shifts into 2-3rd gear
the vehicle goes into limp mode
sudden loss of power and speed
the vehicle accelerates rapidly and unexpectedly
the transmission slips between gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the transmission to slip and hesitate, leading to loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips between gears
the vehicle "lugs" or hesitates
the RPM increases suddenly
the vehicle accelerates rapidly and unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood latch can cause the hood to open while driving, obstructing the driver's view and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The hood rattles at high speeds
the hood appears to be opening
the hood latch does not keep the hood tight when closed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: The power steering locks up or becomes extremely difficult to operate
the steering wheel feels loose
abnormal noise heard from the steering column to the steering wheel
the power steering fails when turning
especially to the left
the power steering fails after long drives
the power steering fails when braking or at slow speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to become loose or difficult to operate, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose
abnormal noise heard from the steering column to the steering wheel
two spline shafts in the steering column worn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering gear box can cause the power steering system to leak oil, leading to a fire hazard, and hindered steering.
symptoms: Power steering gear box leaks oil
power steering fluid level gets low
steering is significantly hindered
power steering sprays all over the engine compartment
including the exhaust
which is a significant fire hazard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trailer brake system can cause loss of control, accidents, or damage to the vehicle or trailer.
symptoms: The "Trailer Brake System" warning message appears on the message board
and the check engine warning indicator illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system malfunction can cause inaccurate voltage readings, which may lead to battery drain, electrical component failure, or even fires.
symptoms: The voltage gauge reads between 16 and 17 volts
despite the dealer's testing showing normal readings of 14.4 to 14.7 volts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbags did not deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Wire Damage due to Rodent Infestation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rodent infestation can cause wire damage, leading to electrical system failures, fires, or other safety hazards.
symptoms: Engine light is on
and chewed wires are discovered; the vehicle is not running properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the park assist system can increase the risk of accidents or damage to the vehicle or other objects.
symptoms: The park assist light illuminates while reversing
but the dealer is unable to duplicate the problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel system noise and movement can cause loss of control, accidents, or damage to the vehicle or fuel tank.
symptoms: A loud sloshing noise of fuel comes from the fuel tank
accompanied by a violent and forceful movement from the exterior rear of the vehicle.
